pacman::p_load("tidyverse", "here")
space_df <- read_csv(here::here("data", "space_launches.csv"))
## Rows: 5727 Columns: 11
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (9): tag, launch_date, type, variant, mission, agency, state_code, categ...
## dbl (2): JD, launch_year
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Count how many launches per year
year_counts <- table(space_df$launch_year)
colors <- c("#972631","#4E656E","#817F3B","#64595F","#7A803C")
# background
par(bg = "#68555F")
# Make a pie chart
pie(year_counts,
    main = "Space Pie",
    col = colors,
    labels = names(year_counts),
    density = 20
)
